<GlossaryTerm id="CDR0000450098"><TermName>counseling</TermName><TermPronunciation>(KOWN-suh-ling)</TermPronunciation><TermDefinition><DefinitionText>The process by which a professional counselor helps a person cope with mental or emotional distress, and understand and solve personal problems.</DefinitionText><Dictionary>Cancer.gov</Dictionary><Audience>Patient</Audience></TermDefinition><MediaLink ref="CDR0000714931" type="audio/mpeg" alt="Pronunciation of dictionary term &quot;counseling&quot;" language="en" id="_3"/><MediaLink ref="CDR0000714932" type="audio/mpeg" alt="Pronunciation of dictionary term &quot;orientación&quot;" language="es" id="_4"/><SpanishTermName>orientación</SpanishTermName><SpanishTermDefinition><DefinitionText>Proceso por el cual un consejero profesional ayuda a una persona a enfrentar el sufrimiento mental o emocional, y a comprender y resolver problemas personales. También se llama asesoramiento, consejería y consejo asistido.</DefinitionText><Dictionary>Cancer.gov</Dictionary><Audience>Patient</Audience></SpanishTermDefinition><DateFirstPublished>2006-01-25</DateFirstPublished><DateLastModified>2008-01-09</DateLastModified><RelatedInformation><RelatedExternalRef UseWith="en" xref="https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/coping">Coping with Cancer</RelatedExternalRef><RelatedExternalRef UseWith="es" xref="https://www.cancer.gov/espanol/cancer/sobrellevar">Cómo hacer frente al cáncer</RelatedExternalRef></RelatedInformation></GlossaryTerm>
